deck_description:
Awesome control deck with never-ending resources if you play your cards back. Normal summoning and banishing are the bread and butter of this deck, so use it well. All the low levels birds are banished when they leave the field and return to your hand on a successful summon of another Winged-Beast monster.

&nbsp;

Ideal opening hand here is Nadir + Robina. Activate Nadir, send your choice of ED monster (varies on need) and add Ecclesia. Normal summon Robina, search and summon Eaglen. Search Empen off of Eaglen and normal summon. Add Map or Unknown Winds (if you opened map) and normal summon Ecclesia off of Empen. Search Punishment, set and pass. Map gives you a summon of their normal summon, giving you the chance to summon birds and turbo out whatever monster you need. Notable monsters here are Raiza to remove your opponents board and Apex Avian for a free negate.

Why is Crystal Beast Rainbow Dragon not in the TCG yet?

&nbsp;

Also we now have 16 ways to open our playmaker Sapphire Pegasus

Using Branded Fusion combo you can easily summon Dragoon or Winda, but did you know you can summon Blue-Eyes Tyrant Dragon too? And Tyrant open a window for trap cards!

Even as Tyrant and Dragoon share the same material(hex-sealed fusion), you can still use them two in the same game because of Rubellion the Divineflame Dragon recycling effects.

You can trade these psy-frames for some Dogmatika, more traps or maybe Dinoruffia... I think this is going to be the next deck.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

GLHF

This time, i implemented the new combo that summon dragoon without using any bricks. There's Winda too, but you need to use one shaddoll monster ;-;.

&nbsp;

Dragoon combo(Winda is the same just changing the card you use to summon Albion the Branded Dragon): first you need to have Branded Fusion at hand, which is easy to get, since you have 9 searchers (including branded opening) +3 copies of Branded Fusion. Activate Branded Fusion and summon Albion the Branded Dragon using Fallen od Albaz + The Light - Hex-Sealed Fusion(or Qadshaddol Keios to get Winda) ~Albion trigger its effects and fusion summon Dragoon(or in case you send Keios to the GY Winda) using only the monster in the GY~ that's all. You can do some variations, but they are situational and don't really change the final product.

